data.title: Elton Brand on win by 76ers

data.text:
Andre Iguodala scored 24 points and Andre Miller added 21 as the 76ers welcomed the return of Elton Brand to the lineup with a 116-110 victory over the New York Knicks last night in Philadelphia.

Brand, who missed 16 games after dislocating his right shoulder on Dec. 17, had six points in 13 minutes off the bench. He entered the game for the first time with 1:26 left in the first quarter.

Samuel Dalembert had 10 points and 17 rebounds for the Sixers, who have won 8-of-9 games.

Heat 103, Magic 97 – Dwyane Wade scored 27 points, Mario Chalmers added 20 and host Miami snapped a 10-game losing streak against Orlando.

Udonis Haslem added 12 points – including two huge baskets down the stretch – for Miami.

Cavaliers 102, Jazz 97 – LeBron James scored 33 points, pulled down 14 rebounds and was just one assist short of a triple-double as Cleveland held off Utah in Salt Lake City.

Mo Williams added 25 points and four assists, including three alley-oops to James, as the Cavs closed out a four-game trip with their third straight win.

Nets 99, Grizzlies 88 – Vince Carter scored 23 points and Devin Harris added 17 points and eight assists as visiting New Jersey snapped a five-game losing skid.

O.J. Mayo scored 23 for Memphis, which lost its ninth straight game.

Trail Blazers 100, Wizards 87 – Brandon Roy had 22 points with 10 steals and seven assists to lead host Portland past Washington.

Caron Butler served up 31 points along with 10 rebounds for the Wizards.

Bucks 106, Kings 104 – Luc Richard Mbah a Moute hit a free throw with 3.3 seconds to go and Richard Jefferson scored 20 points for host Milwaukee.
